# Project Context

**Finpath** — lifetime Canadian wealth planner (Buy vs Rent) with HELOC strategy modeling, registered-account constraints, and retirement projections.

## Stack (authoritative)

- Next.js 15 App Router, React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind, Recharts
- Neon Postgres (`@neondatabase/serverless`) + Vercel
- Tests: Vitest
- Package manager: npm

## High-signal files

- Engine: `src/lib/buyingProjection.ts`
- BC purchase taxes: `src/lib/bcPurchaseTaxes.ts`
- Income tax: `src/lib/canadianTax.ts`
- Types/defaults: `src/types/buying.ts`
- App shell: `app/layout.tsx`
- Dashboard route: `app/page.tsx`, `src/components/dashboard/DashboardPage.tsx`
- Plan route: `app/plan/page.tsx`, `src/components/planner/PlannerWorkspace.tsx`
- Track route: `app/track/page.tsx`, `src/components/track/TrackPage.tsx`
- Settings route: `app/settings/page.tsx`, `src/components/settings/SettingsPage.tsx`
- Planner sections: `src/components/planner/*`
- IA source of truth: `design/ia/navigation.md`
- Persistence API (legacy): `app/api/scenarios/route.ts` → `finpath_legacy_scenarios`
- Persistence API (actuals): `app/api/actuals/route.ts` → `finpath_monthly_actuals`
- Storage helpers: `src/lib/storage.ts`, `src/lib/actuals.ts`
- Domain model: `src/types/domain.ts`
- Canonical rule doc: `src/lib/__tests__/FINANCE_RULES.md`

## Domain anchors

- Funding waterfall: Cash on hand → FHSA → RRSP (HBP cap) → TFSA → Non-Registered
- HELOC strategy toggle: dividend-first vs growth-first
- User-configurable retirement withdrawal ordering
- BC-specific PTT/GST/CMHC handling

## Working conventions

- Treat `FINANCE_RULES.md` as test oracle for domain math.
- Keep projection logic pure and deterministic.
- Anonymous users: local draft persistence only (`localStorage`).
- Authenticated users: session-scoped Neon persistence via `/api/scenarios` (legacy) and `/api/actuals` (no client-controlled identity fallback).
- Database tables use `finpath_` prefix (target model) or `finpath_legacy_` prefix (transitional — do not extend). See `data-and-persistence` rule for details.
- Preserve the top-level product shell: `Dashboard`, `Plan`, `Track`, `Settings`.
- Treat `Plan` and `Track` as different workflows with different state and UI needs; do not collapse them back into one overloaded page.
- Check `design/ia/navigation.md` before changing route structure, top-level navigation labels, or planner section grouping.
- Known discrepancies and intentional gaps are tracked only in `FINANCE_RULES.md` (avoid duplicating them here).
